This directory is where users should put their own scripts to override or add to
the default bash configuration defined in the other directories.

Examples of things you may want to do in this directory:

1) Override important environment variables. For example:

    export EDITOR=
    export FCEDIT=          # editor to use to edit bash commands (see 'help fc')
    export XEDITOR=
    export GIT_EDITOR=      # editor to use to edit git log messages, etc.
    export PAGER=
    export MANPAGER=        # pager to use for viewing man pages

2) Copy-paste useful things from .bash/*/*optional* scripts.

3) Personal aliases and functions that other users probably aren't interested in
   (if others might be interested in them, please request them to be included in
   the standard .bash/*/*.bash scripts).

4) Source one of the scripts in the .bash/themes directory.

5) Temporary or project-specific stuff that you don't want to mix with other configs.

